addLimOrderWithX(address,int24,uint128,b.notice: Add a limit order (selling x) in the pool.

params.data: any data that should be passed through to the callback
params.point: point of the order, be sure to be times of pointDelta

returns.acquireY: amount of tokenY acquired if there is a limit order to sell y before adding

addLimOrderWithY(address,int24,uint128,b.notice: Add a limit order (selling y) in the pool.

params.data: any data that should be passed through to the callback
params.point: point of the order, be sure to be times of pointDelta

returns.acquireX: amount of tokenX acquired if there exists a limit order to sell x before adding

assignLimOrderEarnX(int24,uint128,bool).notice: Mark a given amount of tokenX in a limitorder(selly and earn x) as assigned.

params.assignX: max amount of tokenX to mark assigned
params.fromLegacy: true for assigning earned token from legacyEarnX
params.point: point (log Price) of seller's limit order,be sure to be times of pointDelta

assignLimOrderEarnY(int24,uint128,bool).notice: Mark a given amount of tokenY in a limitorder(sellx and earn y) as assigned.

params.assignY: max amount of tokenY to mark assigned
params.fromLegacy: true for assigning earned token from legacyEarnY
params.point: point (log Price) of seller's limit order,be sure to be times of pointDelta

burn(int24,int24,uint128).notice: Decrease a given amount of liquidity from msg.sender's liquidities.

returns.amountX: The amount of tokenX should be refund after burn
returns.amountY: The amount of tokenY should be refund after burn

collect(address,int24,int24,uint256,uint.notice: Collect tokens (fee or refunded after burn) from a liquidity.

params.amountXLim: max amount of tokenX the owner wants to collect
params.amountYLim: max amount of tokenY the owner wants to collect
params.recipient: the address which should receive the collected tokens

collectFeeCharged().notice: Collect charged fee, only factory's chargeReceiver can call.

collectLimOrder(address,int24,uint128,ui.notice: Collect earned or decreased token from limit order.

params.collectDec: max amount of decreased selling token to collect
params.collectEarn: max amount of earned token to collect
params.isEarnY: direction of this limit order, true for sell y, false for sell x
params.point: point of limit order, be sure to be times of pointDelta

returns.actualCollectDec: actual amount of decresed selling token collected
returns.actualCollectEarn: actual amount of earned token collected

params.deltaX: max amount of tokenX seller wants to decrease
params.point: point of seller's limit order, be sure to be times of pointDelta

returns.legacyAccEarn: legacyAccEarnY of pointOrder at point when calling this interface

params.deltaY: max amount of tokenY seller wants to decrease
params.point: point of seller's limit order, be sure to be times of pointDelta

returns.legacyAccEarn: legacyAccEarnX of pointOrder at point when calling this interface

params.newNextQueueLen: new value of observationNextQueueLen, which should be greater than current observationNextQueueLen

feeChargePercent().notice: Percent to charge from miner's fee.

flash(address,uint256,uint256,bytes).details: The caller needs to implement a IiZiSwapPool#flashCallback callback function
flash(address,uint256,uint256,bytes).notice: Borrow tokenX and/or tokenY and pay it back within a block.

params.amountX: the amount of tokenX to borrow
params.amountY: the amount of tokenY to borrow
params.data: Any data to be passed through to the callback
params.recipient: the address which will receive the tokenY and/or tokenX

limitOrderData(int24).notice: LimitOrder info on a given point.

returns.accEarnX: total amount of earned tokenX(via selling tokenY) by all users at this point as of the last swap
returns.accEarnY: total amount of earned tokenY(via selling tokenX) by all users at this point as of the last swap
returns.earnX: total amount of unclaimed earned tokenX for unlegacy sellingY
returns.earnY: total amount of unclaimed earned tokenY for unlegacy sellingX
returns.legacyAccEarnX: latest recorded 'accEarnX' value when sellingY is clear (legacy)
returns.legacyAccEarnY: latest recorded 'accEarnY' value when sellingX is clear (legacy)
returns.legacyEarnX: total amount of unclaimed earned tokenX for legacy (cleared during swap) sellingY
returns.legacyEarnY: total amount of unclaimed earned tokenY for legacy (cleared during swap) sellingX
returns.sellingX: total amount of tokenX selling on the point
returns.sellingY: total amount of tokenYselling on the point

limitOrderSnapshot(int24,int24).notice: Returns a snapshot infomation of Limit Order in [leftPoint, rightPoint).

params.leftPoint: left endpoint of range, should be times of pointDelta
params.rightPoint: right endpoint of range, should be times of pointDelta

returns.limitOrders: an array of Limit Orders for points in the range    note 1. this function may cost a HUGE amount of gas, be careful to call

liquidity(bytes32).notice: Returns the information about a liquidity by the liquidity's key.

params.key: the liquidity's key is a hash of a preimage composed by the miner(owner), pointLeft and pointRight

returns.lastFeeScaleX_128: fee growth of tokenX inside the range as of the last mint/burn/collect,
returns.lastFeeScaleY_128: fee growth of tokenY inside the range as of the last mint/burn/collect,
returns.tokenOwedX: the computed amount of tokenX miner can collect as of the last mint/burn/collect,
returns.tokenOwedY: the computed amount of tokenY miner can collect as of the last mint/burn/collect

liquiditySnapshot(int24,int24).notice: Returns a snapshot infomation of Liquidity in [leftPoint, rightPoint).

params.leftPoint: left endpoint of range, should be times of pointDelta
params.rightPoint: right endpoint of range, should be times of pointDelta

returns.deltaLiquidities: an array of delta liquidity for points in the range    note 1. delta liquidity here is amount of liquidity changed when cross a point from left to right    note 2. deltaLiquidities only contains points which are times of pointDelta    note 3. this function may cost a ENORMOUS amount of gas, be careful to call

params.data: any data that should be passed through to the callback
params.leftPt: left endpoint of the liquidity, be sure to be times of pointDelta
params.recipient: newly created liquidity will belong to this address
params.rightPt: right endpoint of the liquidity, be sure to be times of pointDelta

returns.amountX: The amount of tokenX that was paid for the liquidity. Matches the value in the callback
returns.amountY: The amount of tokenY that was paid for the liquidity. Matches the value in the callback

params.newFeeChargePercent: new value of feeChargePercent, a nature number range in [0, 100],

observations(uint256).notice: Returns observation data about a specific index.

returns.accPoint: the point multiplied by seconds elapsed for the life of the pool as of the observation timestamp,
returns.init: whether the observation has been initialized and the above values are safe to use

observe(uint32[]).details: Reverts if target timestamp is early than oldest observation in the queueIf you call this method with secondsAgos = [3600, 0]. the average point of this pool during recent hour is (accPoints[1] - accPoints[0]) / 3600
observe(uint32[]).notice: Returns the integral value of point(time) and integral value of 1/liquidity(time)     at some target timestamps (block.timestamp - secondsAgo[i])

params.secondsAgos: describe the target timestamp , targetTimestimp[i] = block.timestamp - secondsAgo[i]

returns.accPoints: integral value of point(time) from 0 to each target timestamp

orderOrEndpoint(int24).notice: Query infomation about a point whether has limit order or is an liquidity's endpoint.

returns.val: endpoint for val&1>0 and has limit order for val&2 > 0

pointBitmap(int16).notice: Returns 256 packed point (statusVal>0) boolean values. See PointBitmap for more information.

returns.accFeeXOut_128: the fee growth on the other side of the point from the current point in tokenX
returns.accFeeYOut_128: the fee growth on the other side of the point from the current point in tokenY
returns.isEndpt: whether the point is an endpoint of a some miner's liquidity, true if liquidSum > 0
returns.liquidDelta: how much liquidity changes when the pool price crosses the point from left to right
returns.liquidSum: the total amount of liquidity that uses the point either as left endpoint or right endpoint

sqrtRate_96().notice: Returns sqrt(1.0001), in 96 bit fixpoint number.

returns.currentPoint: the current point of the pool, 1.0001 ^ currentPoint = price
returns.liquidity: liquidity on the currentPoint (currX * sqrtPrice + currY / sqrtPrice)
returns.locked: whether the pool is locked (only used for checking reentrance)
returns.observationCurrentIndex: the index of the last oracle observation that was written,
returns.observationNextQueueLen: the next maximum number of observations, to be updated when the observation.
returns.observationQueueLen: the current maximum number of observations stored in the pool,
returns.sqrtPrice_96: a 96 fixpoing number describe the sqrt value of current price(tokenX/tokenY)

swapX2Y(address,uint128,int24,bytes).notice: Swap tokenX for tokenY, given max amount of tokenX user willing to pay.

params.amount: the max amount of tokenX user willing to pay
params.data: any data to be passed through to the callback
params.lowPt: the lowest point(price) of x/y during swap

swapX2YDesireY(address,uint128,int24,byt.notice: Swap tokenX for tokenY, given amount of tokenY user desires.

params.data: any data to be passed through to the callback
params.desireY: the amount of tokenY user desires
params.lowPt: the lowest point(price) of x/y during swap

swapY2X(address,uint128,int24,bytes).notice: Swap tokenY for tokenX, given max amount of tokenY user willing to pay.

params.amount: the max amount of tokenY user willing to pay
params.data: any data to be passed through to the callback
params.highPt: the highest point(price) of x/y during swap

swapY2XDesireX(address,uint128,int24,byt.notice: Swap tokenY for tokenX, given amount of tokenX user desires.

params.data: any data to be passed through to the callback
params.desireX: the amount of tokenX user desires
params.highPt: the highest point(price) of x/y during swap

totalFeeXCharged().notice: Amount of charged fee on tokenX.

totalFeeYCharged().notice: Amount of charged fee on tokenY.

userEarnX(bytes32).notice: Returns the information about a user's limit order (sell tokenY and earn tokenX).

params.key: the limit order's key is a hash of a preimage composed by the seller, point

returns.earn: amount of unlegacy earned tokenX in this limit order not assigned
returns.earnAssign: assigned amount of tokenX earned (both legacy and unlegacy) in this limit order
returns.lastAccEarn: total amount of tokenX earned by all users at this point as of the last add/dec/collect
returns.legacyEarn: amount of legacy earned tokenX in this limit order not assgined
returns.sellingDec: amount of tokenY decreased by seller from this limit order
returns.sellingRemain: amount of tokenY not selled in this limit order

userEarnY(bytes32).notice: Returns the information about a user's limit order (sell tokenX and earn tokenY).

params.key: the limit order's key is a hash of a preimage composed by the seller, point

returns.earn: amount of unlegacy earned tokenY in this limit order not assigned
returns.earnAssign: assigned amount of tokenY earned (both legacy and unlegacy) in this limit order
returns.lastAccEarn: total amount of tokenY earned by all users at this point as of the last add/dec/collect
returns.legacyEarn: amount of legacy earned tokenY in this limit order not assgined
returns.sellingDec: amount of tokenX decreased by seller from this limit order
returns.sellingRemain: amount of tokenX not selled in this limit order
